Description: At 4:32 p.m. MDT, Environment Canada meteorologists are tracking a severe thunderstorm capable of producing very strong wind gusts, up to nickel size hail and heavy rain. This thunderstorm is located 25 km northwest of Water Valley and is moving east at 30 km/h. ### Large hail can damage property and cause injury. Severe thunderstorm warnings are issued when imminent or occurring thunderstorms are likely to produce or are producing one or more of the following: large hail, damaging winds, torrential rainfall.
Expires: 2020-07-13T01:31:29-00:00
Originated from CAP Alert: Environment Canada, 2020-07-12T22:33:29-00:00, urn:oid:2.49.0.1.124.3388086517.2020
